Kurento Android SDK
   
   	Kurento Android SDK (KAS) is a framework enabling seamless integration of
   	video conference capabilities within applications. It is built on open 
   	standards and as such complies with IETF and 3GPP specifications. KAS 
   	supports most popular codecs, like AMR, MP2 audio, H.263 H.264, MPEG4
   	and many more in the near future. 
	
	Kurento Android SDK functions are controlled through an easy and flexible API.
  				
