	KAS API consist of two main sections: Control plane and User plane

* Control plane
	
	Provides the User Agent interface for call control. Currently KAS provides
	a SIP based UA.
	   
* User plane

	Implements the media stack control interface. KAS API resembles
	the {{{http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=309}JSR309 Media 
	Server Control API}}, based in two elements that can ebe interconnected:
	NetworkConnection and MediaComponent. NetworkConnection includes relay functions,
	while MediaComponent provides a generic interface
	to multimedia devices, both: presentation and capture.
	All media process complexities are kept hidden to the application,
    that only cares about media distribution topology, connecting 
    physical devices to network interfaces for media transmission and reception.
